Pre-Game Insights: The Honduras national team is set to face Jamaica on September 10, 2024, in their second and final match of the Liga de Naciones de la Concacaf. The team needs a victory to move closer to the quarterfinals, where they will face the United States, Mexico, Canada, and Panama.
Post-Match Reflections: Not available as the match has not occurred yet.
Informacion del Juego: The match will take place on September 10, 2024, at 20:00-08:00 PM in Tegucigalpa, Francisco Morazán, Honduras, at the José de la Paz Herrera 'Chelato' Uclés stadium. The game will be broadcast on Canal 8 & Canal 20 in Honduras, Televisa in Mexico, CBS, Paramount+ (English), TUDN, and Telemundo in the United States, and Concacaf GO & YouTube Concacaf for the rest of the world.
Others: The Honduras national team lost to Jamaica in the previous edition of the Liga de Naciones de la Concacaf by a score of 1-0.
